results.definition: consisting of or involving two parts or components usually in pairs
examples: an egg with a double yolk
dual controls for pilot and copilot
duple (or double) time consists of two (or a multiple of two) beats to a measure

results.definition: having more than one decidedly dissimilar aspects or qualities; public preaching and private influence"- R.W.Emerson
examples: a double (or dual) role for an actor
the office of a clergyman is twofold
every episode has its double and treble meaning"-Frederick Harrison

results.definition: a grammatical number category referring to two items or units as opposed to one item (singular) or more than two items (plural)
examples: ancient Greek had the dual form but it has merged with the plural form in modern Greek
